25|$|<b>Black</b> <b>History</b> Month {{is another}} example of another African-American {{observance}} that has been adopted nationally and its teaching is even required by law in some states. <b>Black</b> <b>History</b> Month is an attempt to focus attention on previously neglected aspects of the American history, chiefly the lives and stories of African Americans. It is observed during the month of February to coincide with the founding of the NAACP and the birthdays of Frederick Douglass, a prominent African-American abolitionist, and Abraham Lincoln, the United States president who signed the Emancipation Proclamation.|$|E
